Mark Steward (@marksteward) on github has contributed to the initial version of this code. I have edited out the unwanted stuff and presented only the bare minimum pritest.py
For more information, 
http://radicalvision.wordpress.com/2011/09/08/how-to-read-an-energy-meter-using-android-device-phone-or-tablet/

Install Python and Pyserial library for 'import serial' to work.
Do the connections according to the information given on my blog above.
Check out where your usb-serial device has mounted. Eg. in Linux it might mount to /dev/ttyUSB0 
or anywhere from COM1 to COM32 in Windows
Run this file.